The paper discusses the principles of organization for a self-constructive artificial intelligence framework, which involves the ability to autonomously construct structures and functionality, simulate and anticipate decisions, and repair functionality. These principles are relevant to several subfields of computer science, including artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural networks (cs.NE), machine learning (cs.LG), systems and control (cs.SY), and robotics (cs.RO). Therefore, these are the most likely sub-categories for this paper.
